    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-12T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-12T21:00:00-05:00" n="498"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-12T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1933—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 13—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Department’s 22, February 11, noon.<note n="19" xml:id="d498fn19">Repeating
                        telegram No. 21, February 11, 11 a.m., from the Ambassador in Brazil, <ref
                            target="#pg_473">p. 473</ref>.</note> Brazilian Minister here delivered
                    note yesterday afternoon to Colombian Minister for Foreign Affairs explaining
                    what Portuguese phrase “in compensation” means. Colombian Government repeats it
                    cannot accept the wording “in compensation”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
